This is according to new report by rights group-Human Rights Watch ,released today.  The 88-page report, entitled 'We Have to Be Worried': The Impact of Lead Contamination on Children's Rights in Kabwe, Zambia," examines the effects of lead contamination in Kabwe, a provincial capital, on children's rights to health, a healthy environment, and education. Channel Africa 's Khumbelo Munzhelele sat down with  Joanna Naples-Mitchell,  Children's rights fellow at human rights watch , and author of the report. And he began by asking her about the key highlights of the report… --channelafrica--